comment4.params=
comment4.target=void\ prepare()
comment4.text=Prepares\ the\ world\ for\ the\ start\ of\ a\ new\ level,\ based\ on\ the\ value\ of\ the\r\n\ level\ class\ variable.\ It\ removes\ all\ actors\ in\ the\ current\ world,\ adds\r\n\ actors\ for\ the\ next\ level\ and\ updates\ the\ displays\ for\ the\ number\ of\ enemies\r\nand\ the\ number\ of\ player\ lives\ left.
comment5.params=
comment5.target=void\ prepareLevel1()
comment5.text=\r\n\ Prepare\ the\ world\ for\ the\ start\ of\ the\ first\ level.\r\n\ That\ is\:\ create\ the\ initial\ objects\ and\ add\ them\ to\ the\ world.\r\n
comment6.params=
comment6.target=void\ showStartScreen()
comment6.text=Shows\ the\ updated\ start\ screen\ display\ for\ the\ start\ of\ this\ level.\r\n\ It\ displays\ the\ current\ level\ number\ and\ the\ number\ of\ remaining\ enemy\r\ntanks\ (this\ method\ is\ also\ called\ after\ a\ level\ is\ reloaded.).
